{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have a tough job to do."},{"time":3000,"text":"You know, when I looked at the profile of the audience here,"},{"time":9000,"text":"with their connotations and design, in all its forms,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and with so much and so many people working"},{"time":18000,"text":"on collaborative and networks, and so on, that I wanted to tell you,"},{"time":23000,"text":"I wanted to build an argument for primary education"},{"time":28000,"text":"in a very specific context."},{"time":30000,"text":"In order to do that in 20 minutes, I have to bring out four ideas --"},{"time":34000,"text":"it's like four pieces of a puzzle."},{"time":37000,"text":"And if I succeed in doing that,"},{"time":40000,"text":"maybe you would go back with the thought"},{"time":43000,"text":"that you could build on, and perhaps help me do my work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"The first piece of the puzzle is remoteness"},{"time":53000,"text":"and the quality of education."},{"time":55000,"text":"Now, by remoteness, I mean two or three different kinds of things."},{"time":60000,"text":"Of course, remoteness in its normal sense, which means"},{"time":63000,"text":"that as you go further and further away"},{"time":66000,"text":"from an urban center, you get to remoter areas."},{"time":71000,"text":"What happens to education?"},{"time":74000,"text":"The second, or a different kind of remoteness"},{"time":76000,"text":"is that within the large metropolitan areas all over the world,"},{"time":81000,"text":"you have pockets, like slums, or shantytowns, or poorer areas,"},{"time":86000,"text":"which are socially and economically remote"},{"time":90000,"text":"from the rest of the city, so it's us and them."},{"time":93000,"text":"What happens to education in that context?"},{"time":95000,"text":"So keep both of those ideas of remoteness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"We made a guess. The guess was that schools in remote areas"},{"time":106000,"text":"do not have good enough teachers."},{"time":109000,"text":"If they do have, they cannot retain those teachers."},{"time":111000,"text":"They do not have good enough infrastructure."},{"time":114000,"text":"And if they had some infrastructure,"},{"time":116000,"text":"they have difficulty maintaining it."},{"time":118000,"text":"But I wanted to check if this is true. So what I did last year was"},{"time":123000,"text":"we hired a car, looked up on Google,"},{"time":128000,"text":"found a route into northern India from New Delhi"},{"time":133000,"text":"which, you know, which did not cross any big cities"},{"time":138000,"text":"or any big metropolitan centers. Drove out about 300 kilometers,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and wherever we found a school, administered a set of standard tests,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and then took those test results and plotted them on a graph."},{"time":155000,"text":"The graph was interesting, although you need to consider it carefully."},{"time":159000,"text":"I mean, this is a very small sample; you should not generalize from it."},{"time":163000,"text":"But it was quite obvious, quite clear,"},{"time":165000,"text":"that for this particular route that I had taken,"},{"time":169000,"text":"the remoter the school was, the worse its results seemed to be."},{"time":174000,"text":"That seemed a little damning,"},{"time":176000,"text":"and I tried to correlate it with things like infrastructure,"},{"time":181000,"text":"or with the availability of electricity, and things like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"To my surprise, it did not correlate."},{"time":187000,"text":"It did not correlate with the size of classrooms."},{"time":190000,"text":"It did not correlate with the quality of the infrastructure."},{"time":195000,"text":"It did not correlate with the poverty levels. It did not correlate."},{"time":199000,"text":"But what happened was that when I administered a questionnaire"},{"time":203000,"text":"to each of these schools, with one single question for the teachers -- which was,"},{"time":207000,"text":"\"Would you like to move to an urban, metropolitan area?\" --"},{"time":212000,"text":"69 percent of them said yes. And as you can see from that,"},{"time":217000,"text":"they say yes just a little bit out of Delhi,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and they say no when you hit the rich suburbs of Delhi --"},{"time":226000,"text":"because, you know, those are relatively better off areas --"},{"time":229000,"text":"and then from 200 kilometers out of Delhi, the answer is consistently yes."},{"time":233000,"text":"I would imagine that a teacher who comes or walks into class"},{"time":236000,"text":"every day thinking that, I wish I was in some other school,"},{"time":240000,"text":"probably has a deep impact on what happens to the results."},{"time":244000,"text":"So it looked as though teacher motivation and teacher migration"},{"time":249000,"text":"was a powerfully correlated thing with what was happening in primary schools,"},{"time":254000,"text":"as opposed to whether the children have enough to eat,"},{"time":257000,"text":"and whether they are packed tightly into classrooms"},{"time":259000,"text":"and that sort of thing. It appears that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"When you take education and technology, then I find in the literature that,"},{"time":268000,"text":"you know, things like websites, collaborative environments --"},{"time":271000,"text":"you've been listening to all that in the morning --"},{"time":273000,"text":"it's always piloted first in the best schools, the best urban schools,"},{"time":279000,"text":"and, according to me, biases the result."},{"time":282000,"text":"The literature -- one part of it, the scientific literature --"},{"time":286000,"text":"consistently blames ET as being over-hyped and under-performing."},{"time":291000,"text":"The teachers always say, well, it's fine, but it's too expensive for what it does."},{"time":297000,"text":"Because it's being piloted in a school where the students are already getting,"},{"time":300000,"text":"let's say, 80 percent of whatever they could do."},{"time":303000,"text":"You put in this new super-duper technology, and now they get 83 percent."},{"time":307000,"text":"So the principal looks at it and says,"},{"time":309000,"text":"3 percent for 300,000 dollars? Forget it."},{"time":312000,"text":"If you took the same technology and piloted it into one of those remote schools,"},{"time":317000,"text":"where the score was 30 percent, and, let's say, took that up to 40 percent --"},{"time":322000,"text":"that will be a completely different thing."},{"time":324000,"text":"So the relative change that ET, Educational Technology, would make,"},{"time":328000,"text":"would be far greater at the bottom of the pyramid than at the top,"},{"time":331000,"text":"but we seem to be doing it the other way about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"So I came to this conclusion that ET should reach"},{"time":337000,"text":"the underprivileged first, not the other way about."},{"time":340000,"text":"And finally came the question of, how do you tackle teacher perception?"},{"time":343000,"text":"Whenever you go to a teacher and show them some technology,"},{"time":345000,"text":"the teacher's first reaction is,"},{"time":347000,"text":"you cannot replace a teacher with a machine -- it's impossible."},{"time":353000,"text":"I don't know why it's impossible, but, even for a moment,"},{"time":355000,"text":"if you did assume that it's impossible -- I have a quotation from Sir Arthur C. Clarke,"},{"time":360000,"text":"the science fiction writer whom I met in Colombo,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and he said something which completely solves this problem."},{"time":368000,"text":"He said a teacher than can be replaced by a machine, should be."},{"time":374000,"text":"So, you know, it puts the teacher into a tough bind, you have to think."},{"time":380000,"text":"Anyway, so I'm proposing that an alternative primary education,"},{"time":383000,"text":"whatever alternative you want, is required where schools don't exist,"},{"time":388000,"text":"where schools are not good enough, where teachers are not available"},{"time":391000,"text":"or where teachers are not good enough, for whatever reason."},{"time":394000,"text":"If you happen to live in a part of the world where none of this applies,"},{"time":398000,"text":"then you don't need an alternative education."},{"time":400000,"text":"So far I haven't come across such an area, except for one case. I won't name the area,"},{"time":406000,"text":"but somewhere in the world people said, we don't have this problem,"},{"time":409000,"text":"because we have perfect teachers and perfect schools."},{"time":413000,"text":"There are such areas, but -- anyway, I'd never heard that anywhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"I'm going to talk about children and self-organization,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and a set of experiments which sort of led to this idea"},{"time":426000,"text":"of what might an alternative education be like."},{"time":430000,"text":"They're called the hole-in-the-wall experiments."},{"time":432000,"text":"I'll have to really rush through this. They're a set of experiments."},{"time":437000,"text":"The first one was done in New Delhi in 1999."},{"time":443000,"text":"And what we did over there was pretty much simple."},{"time":447000,"text":"I had an office in those days which bordered a slum, an urban slum,"},{"time":451000,"text":"so there was a dividing wall between our office and the urban slum."},{"time":455000,"text":"They cut a hole inside that wall --"},{"time":457000,"text":"which is how it has got the name hole-in-the-wall --"},{"time":459000,"text":"and put a pretty powerful PC into that hole, sort of embedded into the wall"},{"time":464000,"text":"so that its monitor was sticking out at the other end,"},{"time":467000,"text":"a touchpad similarly embedded into the wall,"},{"time":470000,"text":"put it on high-speed Internet, put the Internet Explorer there,"},{"time":476000,"text":"put it on Altavista.com -- in those days -- and just left it there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"And this is what we saw."},{"time":484000,"text":"So that was my office in IIT. Here's the hole-in-the-wall."},{"time":493000,"text":"About eight hours later, we found this kid."},{"time":499000,"text":"To the right is this eight-year-old child who --"},{"time":504000,"text":"and to his left is a six-year-old girl, who is not very tall."},{"time":509000,"text":"And what he was doing was, he was teaching her to browse."},{"time":513000,"text":"So it sort of raised more questions than it answered."},{"time":518000,"text":"Is this real? Does the language matter,"},{"time":520000,"text":"because he's not supposed to know English?"},{"time":522000,"text":"Will the computer last, or will they break it and steal it"},{"time":525000,"text":"-- and did anyone teach them?"},{"time":527000,"text":"The last question is what everybody said, but you know,"},{"time":529000,"text":"I mean, they must have poked their head over the wall"},{"time":531000,"text":"and asked the people in your office,"},{"time":533000,"text":"can you show me how to do it, and then somebody taught him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"So I took the experiment out of Delhi and repeated it,"},{"time":539000,"text":"this time in a city called Shivpuri in the center of India,"},{"time":545000,"text":"where I was assured that nobody had ever taught anybody anything."},{"time":550000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":554000,"text":"So it was a warm day, and the hole in the wall"},{"time":559000,"text":"was on that decrepit old building. This is the first kid who came there;"},{"time":564000,"text":"he later on turned out to be a 13-year-old school dropout."},{"time":566000,"text":"He came there and he started to fiddle around with the touchpad."},{"time":572000,"text":"Very quickly, he noticed that when he moves his finger on the touchpad"},{"time":575000,"text":"something moves on the screen --"},{"time":576000,"text":"and later on he told me, \"I have never seen a television"},{"time":579000,"text":"where you can do something.\""},{"time":580000,"text":"So he figured that out. It took him over two minutes"},{"time":583000,"text":"to figure out that he was doing things to the television."},{"time":586000,"text":"And then, as he was doing that, he made an accidental click"},{"time":589000,"text":"by hitting the touchpad -- you'll see him do that."},{"time":596000,"text":"He did that, and the Internet Explorer changed page."},{"time":602000,"text":"Eight minutes later, he looked from his hand to the screen,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and he was browsing: he was going back and forth."},{"time":610000,"text":"When that happened, he started calling all the neighborhood children,"},{"time":615000,"text":"like, children would come and see what's happening over here."},{"time":622000,"text":"And by the evening of that day, 70 children were all browsing."},{"time":626000,"text":"So eight minutes and an embedded computer"},{"time":630000,"text":"seemed to be all that we needed there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"So we thought that this is what was happening:"},{"time":637000,"text":"that children in groups can self-instruct themselves"},{"time":640000,"text":"to use a computer and the Internet. But under what circumstances?"},{"time":648000,"text":"At this time there was a -- the main question was about English."},{"time":654000,"text":"People said, you know, you really ought to have this in Indian languages."},{"time":658000,"text":"So I said, have what, shall I translate the Internet"},{"time":661000,"text":"into some Indian language? That's not possible."},{"time":664000,"text":"So, it has to be the other way about."},{"time":666000,"text":"But let's see, how do the children tackle the English language?"},{"time":670000,"text":"I took the experiment out to northeastern India,"},{"time":673000,"text":"to a village called Madantusi,"},{"time":675000,"text":"where, for some reason, there was no English teacher,"},{"time":679000,"text":"so the children had not learned English at all."},{"time":682000,"text":"And I built a similar hole-in-the-wall."},{"time":686000,"text":"One big difference in the villages, as opposed to the urban slums:"},{"time":688000,"text":"there were more girls than boys who came to the kiosk."},{"time":692000,"text":"In the urban slums, the girls tend to stay away."},{"time":696000,"text":"I left the computer there with lots of CDs -- I didn't have any Internet --"},{"time":701000,"text":"and came back three months later."},{"time":705000,"text":"So when I came back there, I found these two kids,"},{"time":709000,"text":"eight- and 12-year-olds, who were playing a game on the computer."},{"time":713000,"text":"And as soon as they saw me they said,"},{"time":717000,"text":"\"We need a faster processor and a better mouse.\""},{"time":720000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":724000,"text":"I was real surprised."},{"time":726000,"text":"You know, how on earth did they know all this?"},{"time":729000,"text":"And they said, \"Well, we've picked it up from the CDs.\""},{"time":731000,"text":"So I said, \"But how did you understand what's going on over there?\""},{"time":734000,"text":"So they said, \"Well, you've left this machine"},{"time":736000,"text":"which talks only in English, so we had to learn English.\""},{"time":739000,"text":"So then I measured, and they were using 200 English words with each other"},{"time":743000,"text":"-- mispronounced, but correct usage --"},{"time":746000,"text":"words like exit, stop, find, save, that kind of thing,"},{"time":752000,"text":"not only to do with the computer but in their day-to-day conversations."},{"time":755000,"text":"So, Madantusi seemed to show that language is not a barrier;"},{"time":759000,"text":"in fact they may be able to teach themselves the language"},{"time":761000,"text":"if they really wanted to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Finally, I got some funding to try this experiment out"},{"time":769000,"text":"to see if these results are replicable, if they happen everywhere else."},{"time":773000,"text":"India is a good place to do such an experiment in,"},{"time":776000,"text":"because we have all the ethnic diversities, all the -- you know,"},{"time":779000,"text":"the genetic diversity, all the racial diversities,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and also all the socio-economic diversities."},{"time":784000,"text":"So, I could actually choose samples to cover a cross section"},{"time":789000,"text":"that would cover practically the whole world."},{"time":793000,"text":"So I did this for almost five years, and this experiment"},{"time":797000,"text":"really took us all the way across the length and breadth of India."},{"time":800000,"text":"This is the Himalayas. Up in the north, very cold."},{"time":803000,"text":"I also had to check or invent an engineering design"},{"time":806000,"text":"which would survive outdoors, and I was using regular, normal PCs,"},{"time":810000,"text":"so I needed different climates, for which India is also great,"},{"time":813000,"text":"because we have very cold, very hot, and so on."},{"time":816000,"text":"This is the desert to the west. Near the Pakistan border."},{"time":828000,"text":"And you see here a little clip of -- one of these villages --"},{"time":832000,"text":"the first thing that these children did was to find a website"},{"time":835000,"text":"to teach themselves the English alphabet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"Then to central India -- very warm, moist, fishing villages,"},{"time":843000,"text":"where humidity is a very big killer of electronics."},{"time":847000,"text":"So we had to solve all the problems we had"},{"time":850000,"text":"without air conditioning and with very poor power,"},{"time":852000,"text":"so most of the solutions that came out used little blasts of air"},{"time":857000,"text":"put at the right places to keep the machines running."},{"time":860000,"text":"I want to just cut this short. We did this over and over again."},{"time":865000,"text":"This sequence is also nice. This is a small child, a six-year-old,"},{"time":869000,"text":"telling his eldest sister what to do."},{"time":871000,"text":"And this happens very often with these computers,"},{"time":873000,"text":"that the younger children are found teaching the older ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"What did we find? We found that six- to 13-year-olds can self-instruct"},{"time":884000,"text":"in a connected environment,"},{"time":886000,"text":"irrespective of anything that we could measure."},{"time":891000,"text":"So if they have access to the computer, they will teach themselves, including intelligence."},{"time":896000,"text":"I couldn't find a single correlation with anything, but it had to be in groups."},{"time":901000,"text":"And that may be of great, you know, interest to this group,"},{"time":905000,"text":"because all of you are talking about groups."},{"time":907000,"text":"So here was the power of what a group of children can do,"},{"time":911000,"text":"if you lift the adult intervention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"Just a quick idea of the measurements."},{"time":918000,"text":"We took standard statistical techniques, so I'm going to not talk about that."},{"time":922000,"text":"But we got a clean learning curve,"},{"time":925000,"text":"almost exactly the same as what you would get in a school."},{"time":928000,"text":"I'll leave it at that,"},{"time":930000,"text":"because, I mean, it sort of says it all, doesn't it?"},{"time":933000,"text":"What could they learn to do?"},{"time":935000,"text":"Basic Windows functions, browsing, painting, chatting and email,"},{"time":940000,"text":"games and educational material, music downloads, playing video."},{"time":943000,"text":"In short, what all of us do."},{"time":945000,"text":"And over 300 children will become computer literate"},{"time":949000,"text":"and be able to do all of these things in six months with one computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":954000,"text":"So, how do they do that?"},{"time":955000,"text":"If you calculated the actual time of access,"},{"time":957000,"text":"it would work out to minutes per day,"},{"time":959000,"text":"so that's not how it's happening."},{"time":961000,"text":"What you have, actually, is there is one child operating the computer."},{"time":966000,"text":"And surrounding him are usually three other children,"},{"time":968000,"text":"who are advising him on what they should do."},{"time":972000,"text":"If you test them, all four will get the same scores in whatever you ask them."},{"time":976000,"text":"Around these four are usually a group of about 16 children,"},{"time":980000,"text":"who are also advising, usually wrongly,"},{"time":983000,"text":"about everything that's going on on the computer."},{"time":986000,"text":"And all of them also will clear a test given on that subject."},{"time":991000,"text":"So they are learning as much by watching as they learn by doing."},{"time":995000,"text":"It seems counter-intuitive to adult learning,"},{"time":998000,"text":"but remember, eight-year-olds live in a society"},{"time":1000000,"text":"where most of the time they are told, don't do this,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"you know, don't touch the whiskey bottle."},{"time":1006000,"text":"So what does the eight-year-old do?"},{"time":1008000,"text":"He observes very carefully how a whiskey bottle should be touched."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And if you tested him,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"he would answer every question correctly on that topic."},{"time":1015000,"text":"So, they seem to be able to acquire very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021000,"text":"So what was the conclusion over the six years of work?"},{"time":1024000,"text":"It was that primary education can happen on its own,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"or parts of it can happen on its own."},{"time":1030000,"text":"It does not have to be imposed from the top downwards."},{"time":1034000,"text":"It could perhaps be a self-organizing system, so that was"},{"time":1040000,"text":"the second bit that I wanted to tell you,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"that children can self-organize and attain an educational objective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046000,"text":"The third piece was on values, and again, to put it very briefly,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"I conducted a test over 500 children spread across all over India,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and asked them -- I gave them about 68 different"},{"time":1059000,"text":"values-oriented questions and simply asked them their opinions."},{"time":1063000,"text":"We got all sorts of opinions. Yes, no or I don't know."},{"time":1067000,"text":"I simply took those questions where I got 50 percent yeses and 50 percent noes --"},{"time":1073000,"text":"so I was able to get a collection of 16 such statements."},{"time":1077000,"text":"These were areas where the children were clearly confused,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"because half said yes and half said no."},{"time":1083000,"text":"A typical example being, \"Sometimes it is necessary to tell lies.\""},{"time":1087000,"text":"They don't have a way to determine which way to answer this question;"},{"time":1092000,"text":"perhaps none of us do."},{"time":1095000,"text":"So I leave you with this third question."},{"time":1097000,"text":"Can technology alter the acquisition of values?"},{"time":1101000,"text":"Finally, self-organizing systems,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"about which, again, I won't say too much"},{"time":1105000,"text":"because you've been hearing all about it."},{"time":1109000,"text":"Natural systems are all self-organizing:"},{"time":1111000,"text":"galaxies, molecules, cells, organisms, societies --"},{"time":1114000,"text":"except for the debate about an intelligent designer."},{"time":1116000,"text":"But at this point in time, as far as science goes,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"it's self-organization."},{"time":1121000,"text":"But other examples are traffic jams, stock market, society"},{"time":1124000,"text":"and disaster recovery, terrorism and insurgency."},{"time":1130000,"text":"And you know about the Internet-based self-organizing systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"So here are my four sentences then."},{"time":1136000,"text":"Remoteness affects the quality of education."},{"time":1140000,"text":"Educational technology should be introduced into remote areas first,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"and other areas later."},{"time":1149000,"text":"Values are acquired; doctrine and dogma are imposed --"},{"time":1155000,"text":"the two opposing mechanisms."},{"time":1157000,"text":"And learning is most likely a self-organizing system."},{"time":1162000,"text":"If you put all the four together, then it gives -- according to me --"},{"time":1167000,"text":"it gives us a goal, a vision, for educational technology."},{"time":1171000,"text":"An educational technology and pedagogy that is digital, automatic,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"fault-tolerant, minimally invasive, connected and self-organized."},{"time":1183000,"text":"As educationists, we have never asked for technology; we keep borrowing it."},{"time":1187000,"text":"PowerPoint is supposed to be considered a great educational technology,"},{"time":1191000,"text":"but it was not meant for education, it was meant for making boardroom presentations."},{"time":1195000,"text":"We borrowed it. Video conferencing. The personal computer itself."},{"time":1199000,"text":"I think it's time that the educationists made their own specs,"},{"time":1202000,"text":"and I have such a set of specs. This is a brief look at that."},{"time":1206000,"text":"And such a set of specs should produce the technology"},{"time":1210000,"text":"to address remoteness, values and violence."},{"time":1213000,"text":"So I thought I'd give it a name -- why don't we call it \"outdoctrination.\""},{"time":1219000,"text":"And could this be a goal for educational technology in the future?"},{"time":1224000,"text":"So I want to leave that as a thought with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1228000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}